<TITLE> Govt launches probe into Eidgah fiasco </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 24 (bdnews24.com)The government on Thursday formed a two-member committee to probe the National Eidgah ground fiasco during the Eid congregation, the local government minister said. The committee headed by the local government additional secretary Syed Mahbub Hasan has been asked to submit a report within a week, Syed Ashraful Islam told reporters at the Secretariat. It has also been empowered to co-opt any number of additional members, as necessary, he said, accompanied by his deputy Jahangir Kabir Nanak and secretary Manzoor Hossain. The devotees on the Eid day on Monday got drenched in the rains while offering prayers in the grounds that were inundated under inches deep water, as there were no tarpaulin covers overhead. People expressed dissatisfaction with the government arrangements for the Eid prayers. The minister said the government will take appropriate steps to address the mismanagement after the the report of the two-member committee is in. Dhaka City Corporation is responsible for maintenance of the National Eidgah, he said. The government has decided to probe why the agencies or people responsible for its management failed to do so, the minister added. On what the government has been deliberating about improving the facilities at Sholakia, the largest Eid congregation ground in the country, Ashraf said the locals did nt like the government proposal of paving the sprawling grounds. The government then asked the local engineers to prepare and forward appropriate facelift plans. He said the Sholakia grounds in Mymensingh will be raised by packing its base with additional layers of sand and earth and then the surface will be planted with grass. Drains will be built across the grounds to ensure proper drainage of rainwater, Ashraf added. b
